{"parse":{"title":"San Giobbe Altarpiece","pageid":32136055,"revid":842201379,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vevent\" style=\"width:22em;width: 22em; line-height: 1.4em; text-align: left; float:right;\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" class=\"summary\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-size: 125%; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic\">San Giobbe Altarpiece</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Accademia_-_Pala_di_San_Giobbe_by_Giovanni_Bellini.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Accademia - Pala di San Giobbe by Giovanni Bellini.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/aa/Accademia_-_Pala_di_San_Giobbe_by_Giovanni_Bellini.jpg/300px-Accademia_-_Pala_di_San_Giobbe_by_Giovanni_Bellini.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"514\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/aa/Accademia_-_Pala_di_San_Giobbe_by_Giovanni_Bellini.jpg/450px-Accademia_-_Pala_di_San_Giobbe_by_Giovanni_Bellini.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/aa/Accademia_-_Pala_di_San_Giobbe_by_Giovanni_Bellini.jpg/600px-Accademia_-_Pala_di_San_Giobbe_by_Giovanni_Bellini.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"3937\" data-file-height=\"6749\" /></a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Artist</th><td class=\"attendee\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Giovanni_Bellini\" title=\"Giovanni Bellini\">Giovanni Bellini</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Year</th><td>\nc. 1487</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Medium</th><td class=\"category\">\nOil on panel</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Dimensions</th><td>\n471&#160;cm&#32;\u00d7&#160;258&#160;cm&#32;(185&#160;in&#32;\u00d7&#160;102&#160;in)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Location</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Gallerie_dell%27Accademia\" title=\"Gallerie dell&#39;Accademia\">Gallerie dell'Accademia</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Venice\" title=\"Venice\">Venice</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The <i><b>San Giobbe Altarpiece</b></i> (Italian: <i>Pala di San Giobbe</i>) is a c. 1487 <a href=\"/wiki/Oil_painting\" title=\"Oil painting\">oil painting</a> by the Italian Renaissance master <a href=\"/wiki/Giovanni_Bellini\" title=\"Giovanni Bellini\">Giovanni Bellini</a>, now in the <a href=\"/wiki/Gallerie_dell%27Accademia\" title=\"Gallerie dell&#39;Accademia\">Gallerie dell'Accademia</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Venice\" title=\"Venice\">Venice</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Description\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Description</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Sources\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Sources</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=San_Giobbe_Altarpiece&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>This altarpiece is one of the masterworks of Bellini's mature period, and was painted for the second left altar of the church of <a href=\"/wiki/San_Giobbe\" title=\"San Giobbe\">San Giobbe</a> in Venice. It was probably inspired by the <a href=\"/wiki/San_Cassiano_Altarpiece\" title=\"San Cassiano Altarpiece\">San Cassiano Altarpiece</a> by <a href=\"/wiki/Antonello_da_Messina\" title=\"Antonello da Messina\">Antonello da Messina</a> (1475-1476), and absorbed and further developed that work's innovations. Yet, as the dating of Bellini's painting is uncertain, such dependency cannot be proved.\nThe work is among Bellini's most famous, a claim made as early as <i>De Urbe Sito</i>, a description of Venice by <a href=\"/wiki/Marco_Antonio_Sabellico\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Marco Antonio Sabellico\">Marco Antonio Sabellico</a> (1487-1491).\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tleft\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:242px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Pala_di_san_giobbe_06.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/53/Pala_di_san_giobbe_06.jpg/240px-Pala_di_san_giobbe_06.jpg\" width=\"240\" height=\"209\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/53/Pala_di_san_giobbe_06.jpg/360px-Pala_di_san_giobbe_06.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/53/Pala_di_san_giobbe_06.jpg/480px-Pala_di_san_giobbe_06.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1150\" data-file-height=\"1000\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Pala_di_san_giobbe_06.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Detail of the musician angels.</div></div></div>\n<p>The depiction of Saints <a href=\"/wiki/Saint_Sebastian\" title=\"Saint Sebastian\"> Sebastian</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Job_(biblical_figure)\" title=\"Job (biblical figure)\">Job</a> indicates that the painting might be created in connection with the plague probably that of 1987<sup>[correct date?]</sup>. The dating of the work is disputed, ranging from the early 1470s to the late 1480s.  <a href=\"/wiki/Jacopo_Sansovino\" title=\"Jacopo Sansovino\">Jacopo Sansovino</a> wrote in 1581 that the work for San Giobbe was Bellini's first using oil painting, which would imply an earlier date, nearer to Antonello's altarpiece. Yet, many scholars have disputed such claim.\n</p><p>The altarpiece remained in the church of San Giobbe until 1814-1818<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Description\">Description</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=San_Giobbe_Altarpiece&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Description\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The work can be read as an example of <a href=\"/wiki/Holy_Conversation\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Holy Conversation\">Holy Conversation</a>: Mary sits on a tall marble throne, holding the Child; at her feet are three musician angels, while at the side are, in symmetrical positions, six saints. They are, on the left, Sts. <a href=\"/wiki/Francis_of_Assisi\" title=\"Francis of Assisi\">Francis</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/John_the_Baptist\" title=\"John the Baptist\">John the Baptist</a> and Job; on the right, Sts. <a href=\"/wiki/Saint_Dominic\" title=\"Saint Dominic\">Dominic</a>, Sebastian and <a href=\"/wiki/Louis_of_Toulouse\" title=\"Louis of Toulouse\">Louis of Toulouse</a>. The child's feature are very similar to those in the <a href=\"/wiki/Contarini_Madonna\" title=\"Contarini Madonna\">Contarini Madonna</a>, also housed in the Accademia Gallery.\n</p>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"width:22em;width: 210px; float: right; clear: right; margin:0 0 1.0em 1.0em\"><caption>External video</caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Pala_di_san_giobbe_04.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Pala di san giobbe 04.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f5/Pala_di_san_giobbe_04.jpg/210px-Pala_di_san_giobbe_04.jpg\" width=\"210\" height=\"334\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f5/Pala_di_san_giobbe_04.jpg/315px-Pala_di_san_giobbe_04.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f5/Pala_di_san_giobbe_04.jpg/420px-Pala_di_san_giobbe_04.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"881\" data-file-height=\"1400\" /></a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;text-align: left\">\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1b/Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg/16px-Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1b/Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg/24px-Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1b/Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg/32px-Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"128\" data-file-height=\"128\" /> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://smarthistory.khanacademy.org/bellinis-san-giobbe-altarpiece.html\">Bellini's <i>San Giobbe Altarpiece</i></a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Smarthistory\" title=\"Smarthistory\">Smarthistory</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The upper part features a perspective coffered ceiling, flanked with pillars which are copies of the real ones at the original altar. Behind the Madonna is a dark niche. In the latter's half-dome is a gilt mosaic decoration in the Venetian style.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=San_Giobbe_Altarpiece&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Rugolo, Ruggero (2013). <i>Venise - O\u00f9 trouver Bellini, Carpaccio, Titen, Tintoret, V\u00e9ron\u00e8se</i> (in French). Scala. p.&#160;12. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9788881173891\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9788881173891\">9788881173891</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Venise+-+O%C3%B9+trouver+Bellini%2C+Carpaccio%2C+Titen%2C+Tintoret%2C+V%C3%A9ron%C3%A8se&amp;rft.pages=12&amp;rft.pub=Scala&amp;rft.date=2013&amp;rft.isbn=9788881173891&amp;rft.aulast=Rugolo&amp;rft.aufirst=Ruggero&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASan+Giobbe+Altarpiece\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=San_Giobbe_Altarpiece&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<table role=\"presentation\" class=\"mbox-small plainlinks sistersitebox\" style=\"background-color:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;color:#000\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td class=\"mbox-image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/30px-Commons-logo.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"40\" class=\"noviewer\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/45px-Commons-logo.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Comm